WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:04.588
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>
We're not picking a name
until B‐day.

00:04.588 --> 00:06.173
I had no idea you were
this superstitious.

00:06.173 --> 00:07.674
I just wear a talisman
a drug lord gave me

00:07.674 --> 00:10.677
to keep evil spirits away
from my unborn child.

00:10.677 --> 00:12.012
Nice of you
to see us off.

00:12.012 --> 00:13.222
Gun!
[ Gunfire ]

00:13.222 --> 00:15.140
Killing Cesar
would be unsatisfying.

00:15.140 --> 00:17.893
But if Cesar's child
were to die ‐‐

00:17.893 --> 00:19.102
We knew a gang war
was coming, right?

00:19.102 --> 00:20.687
Which presents
an opportunity.

00:20.687 --> 00:22.105
You want me to go back in
as the chemist?

00:22.105 --> 00:24.775
No!
You abducted me

00:24.775 --> 00:26.985
when you know
what I have been through!

00:26.985 --> 00:28.862
Do you still want this?

00:28.862 --> 00:30.572
Yeah.

00:30.572 --> 00:33.867
[ Auf Der Mar's
"Followed the Waves" plays ]

00:33.867 --> 00:40.457
♪♪

00:40.457 --> 00:43.168
[ Siren wails in distance ]

00:43.168 --> 00:44.211
♪ Feel me
sneakin' around again ♪

00:44.211 --> 00:45.462
Harper: Tell me.

00:45.462 --> 00:47.464
Lucy:
My cover is Nova Lin,

00:47.464 --> 00:50.050
former chemistry major
with a bent moral compass

00:50.050 --> 00:52.052
and a fortune
in student loan debt.

00:52.052 --> 00:54.680
Court records will show
you made bail yesterday,

00:54.680 --> 00:56.765
and your cover
will be fully papered.

00:56.765 --> 01:01.019
So you are back out in the wild
and open for business.

01:01.019 --> 01:03.730
You will make camp at
the Hollywood Premiere Motel.

01:03.730 --> 01:06.358
It is [Chuckles dryly]
the bottom of the barrel,

01:06.358 --> 01:08.694
the last branch you hit
on your way down,

01:08.694 --> 01:10.112
and it will
send the message

01:10.112 --> 01:12.698
that you are desperate
to make money.

01:12.698 --> 01:14.950
♪ My heart lies to you ♪

01:14.950 --> 01:17.160
Tell me the number‐one rule
of undercover work.

01:17.160 --> 01:19.871
No case is worth my life.

01:19.871 --> 01:21.707
At any time
before the operation begins,

01:21.707 --> 01:23.750
I have the authority
to pull the plug

01:23.750 --> 01:25.627
and pull out of this op.

01:25.627 --> 01:27.504
♪♪

01:27.504 --> 01:30.549
Once I'm out there
and things go sideways,

01:30.549 --> 01:33.385
defend myself or run away.

01:33.385 --> 01:35.637
There is no shame
in running away.

01:35.637 --> 01:40.559
♪ I lie ♪

01:40.559 --> 01:43.437
♪♪

01:43.437 --> 01:46.315
Your mission is
to identify everyone

01:46.315 --> 01:49.901
conspiring to manufacture
and distribute narcotics.

01:49.901 --> 01:51.611
Stick to that objective.

01:51.611 --> 01:54.239
Unless your targets are also
conspiring to commit murder,

01:54.239 --> 01:57.784
make a mental note
and move on.

01:57.784 --> 02:01.830
Illegal weapons, stolen
property, cars ‐‐ ignore it.

02:01.830 --> 02:04.416
You are not to take action
on misdemeanors

02:04.416 --> 02:06.918
unless it advances
this case.

02:06.918 --> 02:10.130
Policy, procedure,
and the law ‐‐

02:10.130 --> 02:11.757
those are your guidelines.

02:11.757 --> 02:14.635
You can defend yourself.
You can defend others.

02:14.635 --> 02:18.930
You can even use deadly force
without revealing your identity.

02:18.930 --> 02:20.932
But whenever possible,

02:20.932 --> 02:24.269
talk your way
out of a dangerous situation.

02:24.269 --> 02:28.065
♪ I followed the waves to you ♪

02:28.065 --> 02:29.941
This isn't like
the deal we did with Coco.

02:29.941 --> 02:31.360
This time, you'll be alone.

02:31.360 --> 02:33.737
There is no surveillance van
outside.

02:33.737 --> 02:35.989
There is no rescue team
next door.

02:35.989 --> 02:38.283
Your only contact
will be with me,

02:38.283 --> 02:41.912
making regular reports
at both 9:00 a. m. and midnight.

02:41.912 --> 02:43.205
Now for the hard part.

02:43.205 --> 02:44.915
At least it was
for me, anyway.

02:46.166 --> 02:47.125
Let me have it.

02:48.669 --> 02:52.130
♪ Between my fire sighs
and my burning eyes ♪

02:52.130 --> 02:54.216
♪ My heart burns wildly
in his eyes ♪

02:54.216 --> 02:56.718
Final words,
and listen closely ‐‐

02:56.718 --> 02:59.763
There is a chance
that nothing will happen,

02:59.763 --> 03:01.515
that Salonga
won't make contact,

03:01.515 --> 03:03.266
and that the only thing
you will get

03:03.266 --> 03:06.019
is a paid vacation
to the Hep C Motel.

03:06.019 --> 03:07.646
But you can never...
[ Doorknob rattles ]

03:07.646 --> 03:09.648
...let down your guard.
[ Loud thump ]

03:09.648 --> 03:10.982
Never relax.

03:10.982 --> 03:12.359
[ Doorknob rattling ]

03:12.359 --> 03:15.737
Because if it comes,
<i>when</i> it comes,

03:15.737 --> 03:18.615
you will have to do
everything right.

03:18.615 --> 03:21.076
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

03:21.076 --> 03:23.245
Because one wrong word,

03:23.245 --> 03:24.830
one wrong move...
[ Man retching ]

03:24.830 --> 03:27.082
...one wrong look,

03:27.082 --> 03:29.543
and you're dead.

03:29.543 --> 03:32.712
♪♪

03:34.589 --> 03:35.882
[ Knock on door ]

03:40.637 --> 03:42.013
Hello!

03:42.013 --> 03:43.682
Hi.
I'm sorry to bother you.

03:43.682 --> 03:45.016
I'm dog‐sitting
for your neighbors,

03:45.016 --> 03:46.351
and I kind of
locked myself out.

03:46.351 --> 03:49.688
Here you go.
Oh, my God. Yes.

03:49.688 --> 03:51.440
Not sure how much time
you've spent in public

03:51.440 --> 03:52.649
wearing only a towel,

03:52.649 --> 03:54.025
but it's terrifying.

03:54.025 --> 03:55.610
Um, did you want to come in?

03:55.610 --> 03:58.071
You're not
a serial killer, are you?

03:58.071 --> 03:59.906
Not that that wouldn't be
the perfect bookend

03:59.906 --> 04:01.908
to this morning from hell.

04:01.908 --> 04:03.827
Well, I'm actually
a police officer,

04:03.827 --> 04:06.580
so the truth is, I'm ‐‐
I'm sworn to protect you.

04:06.580 --> 04:08.123
Oh. Me, personally?

04:08.123 --> 04:10.584
You, e‐especially.

04:10.584 --> 04:12.002
[ Exhales sharply ]

04:12.002 --> 04:13.879
Uh, s‐so, I‐I'm imagining
the dog got out

04:13.879 --> 04:15.255
while you were, uh,
getting into the shower?

04:15.255 --> 04:17.132
That little ass
was sitting on the lawn,

04:17.132 --> 04:18.758
staring at me
through the window.

04:18.758 --> 04:20.552
So I threw on a towel,
went out to get him,

04:20.552 --> 04:23.263
and, well,
the rest is obvious.

04:23.263 --> 04:24.723
Which house
are you staying in?

04:24.723 --> 04:26.892
The green craftsman.
Ronnie and Dylan's place.

04:26.892 --> 04:28.435
I think they gave me
a spare key.

04:28.435 --> 04:30.395
[ Gasps ]
My luck is turning around.

04:30.395 --> 04:31.938
I'm Bailey, by the way.

04:31.938 --> 04:34.775
John. Uh, how do you know
Ronnie and Dylan?

04:34.775 --> 04:36.067
I work with Ronnie.

04:36.067 --> 04:37.736
You're a firefighter.
Yeah.

04:37.736 --> 04:39.988
But you can't ever
tell Ronnie about this,

04:39.988 --> 04:42.407
'cause the firehouse would never
let me live it down.

04:42.407 --> 04:45.035
No problem.
It'll be our first secret.

04:45.035 --> 04:47.162
I like that.

04:48.830 --> 04:50.332
And I love your place.

04:50.332 --> 04:52.292
Thank you.
I put a lot of work into it.

04:52.292 --> 04:54.669
Well, you got skills.

04:54.669 --> 04:56.838
You live here alone?

04:56.838 --> 04:59.382
I do.

04:59.382 --> 05:01.134
And I‐I found it.

05:01.134 --> 05:04.846
So, um, now, do you need
any help, uh, finding the dog?

05:04.846 --> 05:06.807
No.
He's back in the house.

05:06.807 --> 05:08.809
I don't know how,
but when I got outside,

05:08.809 --> 05:10.435
he was in the bathroom
staring at me.

05:10.435 --> 05:13.146
And I swear that little bastard
was laughing.

05:13.146 --> 05:15.607
To be honest, I‐I've never
really cared for him.

05:15.607 --> 05:17.484
[ Chuckles ] Really?
Yeah. Oh, yeah.

05:17.484 --> 05:19.069
I mean, he's so cute,
but he so knows it.

05:19.069 --> 05:21.655
I know.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.031
Thank you for saving me.

05:23.031 --> 05:25.283
I will return
the sweatshirt to you.

05:25.283 --> 05:27.619
Uh, well,
my shift ends at 8:00.

05:27.619 --> 05:28.870
Maybe I could grab some takeout
on the way home.

05:28.870 --> 05:30.580
We could spend dinner

05:30.580 --> 05:32.290
plotting your revenge
against your canine nemesis.

05:32.290 --> 05:33.792
I'd like that.

05:33.792 --> 05:36.253
Then it's a date.

05:36.253 --> 05:37.504
I'll wear my fancy towel.

05:37.504 --> 05:40.382
[ Laughs ]

05:40.382 --> 05:41.967
Thanks again.
Bye.

05:46.221 --> 05:48.265
Your mom sent
another stroller.

05:48.265 --> 05:50.183
[ Sighs ] How many kids
does she think we're having?

05:50.183 --> 05:52.102
[ Knock on door ]

05:53.562 --> 05:55.605
Uh...Tim and Jackson
are here.

05:55.605 --> 05:56.857
Good morning.
[ Door closes ]

05:56.857 --> 05:59.943
[ Dramatic music plays ]

05:59.943 --> 06:03.446
There's bad news. And you think
a riot shield will save you.

06:03.446 --> 06:05.615
Save us? N‐No.

06:05.615 --> 06:08.493
Protect us from major
bodily injury? Hopefully.

06:08.493 --> 06:10.620
Must be really bad
if you brought Jackson.

06:10.620 --> 06:13.206
I'm here
for my calming presence.

06:13.206 --> 06:15.458
I mean, who can be angry
looking at that face?

06:15.458 --> 06:16.835
What happened?

06:16.835 --> 06:19.379
I got a call this morning
about Ralph Hall.

06:19.379 --> 06:20.589
No.

06:20.589 --> 06:22.173
Wait,
why is that name familiar?

06:22.173 --> 06:25.343
The feds, uh, discovered
that his venue was being used

06:25.343 --> 06:27.470
as a cover
for money laundering.

06:27.470 --> 06:28.680
His venue?

06:28.680 --> 06:30.223
Mm‐hmm.

06:30.223 --> 06:32.142
<i>My</i> venue.

06:32.142 --> 06:34.269
Our wedding venue.
Jackson: Yes.

06:34.269 --> 06:38.607
And at 5:04 this morning,
it was...

06:38.607 --> 06:40.650
seized by the FBI.

06:40.650 --> 06:44.195
♪♪

06:44.195 --> 06:46.573
[ Laughing ]

06:46.573 --> 06:53.622
♪♪

06:53.622 --> 06:55.081
Angela.

06:55.081 --> 06:57.500
Oh, it's over.

06:57.500 --> 06:59.544
What? No, no, no.
We ‐‐ We can find another place.

06:59.544 --> 07:01.921
No. We won't.

07:01.921 --> 07:05.592
I'm done. We're getting married
Saturday at the courthouse.

07:05.592 --> 07:07.552
Okay, we are not getting married
at the courthouse.

07:07.552 --> 07:10.138
Then find someplace, but we're
getting married Saturday,

07:10.138 --> 07:11.640
and I'm done
thinking about it.

07:11.640 --> 07:14.225
I don't need fancy.
I‐I never needed fancy.

07:14.225 --> 07:15.477
I just want to be married.

07:16.686 --> 07:18.355
[ Sighs ]

07:18.355 --> 07:19.814
[ Door opens ]

07:19.814 --> 07:21.483
We're on it!
[ Door closes ]

07:21.483 --> 07:22.484
We?
We?

07:23.443 --> 07:24.986
[ Sighs ]

07:24.986 --> 07:26.780
Sgt. Grey: The war is over.

07:26.780 --> 07:29.366
Word is, the last of Cesar's
lieutenants

07:29.366 --> 07:32.661
have kissed La Fiera's ring
and joined Malos Dorados.

07:32.661 --> 07:35.038
In less than two weeks,
Sandra de la Cruz has become

07:35.038 --> 07:36.831
the second‐biggest player
in Southern California.

07:36.831 --> 07:38.625
And she is not slowing down.

07:38.625 --> 07:40.960
We are hearing that any crew
that is unaffiliated

07:40.960 --> 07:42.629
is getting pressured
to join her.

07:42.629 --> 07:45.340
So talk to your street contacts
and your C. I. s.

07:45.340 --> 07:48.218
Alert Narcotics
of any intel you collect.

07:48.218 --> 07:50.220
Where's Cesar?
Lopez: No one knows.

07:50.220 --> 07:51.763
But Sandra's definitely
hunting him.

07:51.763 --> 07:53.139
You know, if we could
get to him first,

07:53.139 --> 07:54.974
we might be able to flip him.

07:54.974 --> 07:57.769
Use his anger against La Fiera
to sabotage his old operation.

07:57.769 --> 07:59.688
You are not the first
to think of that.

07:59.688 --> 08:02.148
In fact, a task force has been
dedicated to finding him.

08:02.148 --> 08:04.359
But if you think you can succeed
where they've failed,

08:04.359 --> 08:06.486
knock yourself out.
Yes, sir.

08:06.486 --> 08:08.697
Oh, and Smitty will be
your T. O. today.

08:08.697 --> 08:11.533
Sarge, the kid only has
a few days left as a rookie ‐‐

08:11.533 --> 08:14.077
I'm cool with letting him
ride solo today.

08:14.077 --> 08:15.954
You are?
Oh, well, I'm not.

08:15.954 --> 08:17.956
Worth a shot.
Anything else?

08:17.956 --> 08:20.291
Yes, sir.
Lopez's wedding is now Saturday.

08:20.291 --> 08:22.419
And you are all
officially uninvited

08:22.419 --> 08:24.295
unless you hear otherwise.
Spread the word.

08:24.295 --> 08:25.630
Man: Aw, come on.
[ Officers grumbling ]

08:25.630 --> 08:27.257
Guys, it's a <i>first</i> marriage.

08:27.257 --> 08:28.842
Okay. That's it.

08:28.842 --> 08:30.468
Be safe out there.

08:30.468 --> 08:32.178
Okay, so, the wedding
is now on Saturday,

08:32.178 --> 08:33.888
which means
we have two days

08:33.888 --> 08:36.224
to plan and pull off a ceremony
and a reception.

08:36.224 --> 08:38.101
Can you help?

08:38.101 --> 08:41.020
[ Scoffs ]
Are you kidding?

08:41.020 --> 08:43.648
I've been preparing for
this moment my whole life.

08:43.648 --> 08:46.317
Y‐Yeah, except it's got to be
what Angela wants.

08:46.317 --> 08:49.112
Don't worry. I got that message
loud and clear.

08:49.112 --> 08:50.447
But I could use some help.

08:50.447 --> 08:52.032
Oh, well, we figured that,

08:52.032 --> 08:55.160
so we hired you
an elite team.

08:55.160 --> 08:57.704
Powerpuff Girls could totally
take out the Avengers.

08:57.704 --> 08:59.873
No. They don't exist
in the same universe.

08:59.873 --> 09:01.666
That fight
could never happen.

09:01.666 --> 09:03.168
But it could, 'cause it's all
just made up anyway, right?

09:03.168 --> 09:04.294
There are rules.

09:04.294 --> 09:05.879
Okay.
What's the problem?

09:05.879 --> 09:07.714
Silas is being difficult.

09:07.714 --> 09:10.508
Silas has autism, and rules help
him make sense of the world.

09:10.508 --> 09:13.386
Tamara, Silas,
this is my mother, Patrice.

09:13.386 --> 09:14.512
You'll be helping her
today.

09:15.472 --> 09:16.723
Are you okay
with that arrangement?

09:16.723 --> 09:19.142
Oh, of course.

09:19.142 --> 09:22.312
From the outfit,
Tamara clearly has good taste.

09:22.312 --> 09:25.523
And Silas' attention to detail
will be a godsend.

09:25.523 --> 09:27.067
Now, I don't know
about the two of you,

09:27.067 --> 09:30.111
but I do my best work
with a beverage.

09:30.111 --> 09:31.571
Maybe a little food
to go along with it?

09:31.571 --> 09:32.864
Yes, please.

09:32.864 --> 09:34.074
I could eat.

09:35.950 --> 09:37.202
This just might work.

09:37.202 --> 09:38.536
Mm‐hmm.

09:38.536 --> 09:40.455
[ Sighs ]

09:40.455 --> 09:42.707
If you were the entitled
but not too bright son

09:42.707 --> 09:44.125
of a dead drug lord,

09:44.125 --> 09:46.920
betrayed by your people
and hunted by apex predators,

09:46.920 --> 09:48.171
where would you go?

09:48.171 --> 09:49.297
Vegas.

09:49.297 --> 09:50.799
Because?

09:50.799 --> 09:54.052
I know I'm gonna die,
and I want to do it in Sin City.

09:54.052 --> 09:55.428
Can't argue with that.

09:55.428 --> 09:57.972
Smitty, can I ask you
a personal question?

09:57.972 --> 10:01.351
I am currently single
and very open to being set up.

10:01.351 --> 10:03.686
That's not ‐‐ I ‐‐

10:03.686 --> 10:06.731
You must have wanted
more than this

10:06.731 --> 10:08.608
at one point, right?

10:08.608 --> 10:11.861
You had ambition, maybe?

10:11.861 --> 10:14.072
When you were younger?

10:14.072 --> 10:16.491
You want the truth?
I do.

10:16.491 --> 10:20.161
Faulkner wrote, "You cannot swim
for new horizons

10:20.161 --> 10:25.583
until you have courage
to lose sight of the shore."

10:25.583 --> 10:27.127
I like the shore.

10:27.127 --> 10:29.129
Look, I get it.

10:29.129 --> 10:31.965
You want the stink of being
held back as a rookie off you.

10:31.965 --> 10:34.884
And finding Cesar and flipping
him is the way to do it.

10:34.884 --> 10:36.302
But how you gonna
pull that off

10:36.302 --> 10:38.471
as a rookie
with no street intel?

10:38.471 --> 10:40.306
I'm gonna talk
to Cesar's girlfriend.

10:40.306 --> 10:42.142
Half the department's
already taken a run at her.

10:42.142 --> 10:44.686
Yeah, but I saved her life.

10:44.686 --> 10:47.021
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

10:50.733 --> 10:53.987
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:53.987 --> 10:56.072
[ Car horn blares ]

10:56.072 --> 10:57.824
[ Gun clicks ]

11:04.998 --> 11:06.916
[ Car horn beeps ]

11:11.462 --> 11:13.506
You don't look like
housekeeping.

11:13.506 --> 11:15.758
Nova, right?

11:15.758 --> 11:17.844
Like the star.

11:17.844 --> 11:19.387
Who the hell are you?

11:19.387 --> 11:20.972
Dahrio Salonga.

11:20.972 --> 11:22.640
My brother sends
his regards.

11:22.640 --> 11:24.726
Aldo. Yeah,
I met the old man once.

11:24.726 --> 11:26.978
It got me arrested.

11:26.978 --> 11:29.898
Whatever you're here for,
it's a hard pass.

11:29.898 --> 11:31.816
We need a cook.
A good one.

11:31.816 --> 11:33.276
Who can make
a lot of product.

11:33.276 --> 11:34.777
Good quality product.

11:34.777 --> 11:36.613
I said pass.

11:36.613 --> 11:38.031
Your brother runs a leaky ship.

11:38.031 --> 11:39.032
I'm not getting back on board.

11:39.032 --> 11:41.492
Leak's been plugged.
Permanently.

11:41.492 --> 11:43.828
Yeah, he went down ugly.
We even gave it a name ‐‐

11:43.828 --> 11:45.330
The Sato Special.

11:45.330 --> 11:46.998
See, I don't want to
know that.

11:46.998 --> 11:48.625
Just like I don't
want to know you.

11:48.625 --> 11:50.126
Yeah, you do.

11:50.126 --> 11:52.462
We've been watching you.

11:52.462 --> 11:56.174
You're not exactly
on an upward trajectory.

11:56.174 --> 11:58.051
Cooking for us
will get you paid.

11:58.051 --> 12:00.261
You've been watching me?
Had to make sure

12:00.261 --> 12:02.513
you didn't make a deal
with the cops to get bail.

12:02.513 --> 12:03.932
Now we know.

12:03.932 --> 12:06.726
So we're gonna
take a ride together,

12:06.726 --> 12:09.103
do some business.

12:09.103 --> 12:10.772
Ride to where?

12:10.772 --> 12:12.148
You'll see.

12:12.148 --> 12:14.192
Put down the laundry.

12:14.192 --> 12:16.110
Leave the gun
in the basket.

12:16.110 --> 12:18.571
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

12:18.571 --> 12:21.115
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

12:21.115 --> 12:27.956
♪♪

12:27.956 --> 12:29.499
I'm gonna want that back.

12:29.499 --> 12:31.292
Uh‐huh.

12:31.292 --> 12:32.627
Let's go.

12:34.629 --> 12:36.714
Uh...

12:36.714 --> 12:38.591
Can I get a jacket?

12:38.591 --> 12:40.218
Sure.

12:40.218 --> 12:41.844
Thank you.

12:41.844 --> 12:48.226
♪♪

12:48.226 --> 12:54.691
♪♪

12:54.691 --> 12:56.693
Okay, I'm ready.

12:56.693 --> 13:00.113
♪♪

13:00.113 --> 13:02.198
Give me your phone.

13:02.198 --> 13:03.992
What? No.

13:03.992 --> 13:06.577
No. You already
got my gun. No.

13:06.577 --> 13:08.538
I'm not asking.

13:08.538 --> 13:15.211
♪♪

13:15.211 --> 13:16.713
[ Cellphone beeps ]

13:16.713 --> 13:18.589
Now let's go.

13:18.589 --> 13:24.053
♪♪

13:30.852 --> 13:32.186
Reyna.

13:32.186 --> 13:35.481
Look, I already spoke to
a bunch of cops.

13:35.481 --> 13:37.150
I don't know
where Cesar is.

13:37.150 --> 13:39.110
I'm ‐‐
[ Chuckles ] I am sorry.

13:39.110 --> 13:40.611
Who is the happiest baby?

13:40.611 --> 13:43.156
God,
those chubby cheeks, too.

13:43.156 --> 13:45.992
I know I owe you
for everything, okay?

13:45.992 --> 13:47.827
For saving us.

13:47.827 --> 13:50.038
But I don't know
where Cesar is.

13:50.038 --> 13:52.081
I haven't spoken to him
in over a week.

13:52.081 --> 13:53.249
Then who's paying
his paycheck?

13:53.249 --> 13:55.752
Nobody.
He's my cousin Hector.

13:55.752 --> 13:57.754
I got two more cousins
even bigger back at the house.

13:57.754 --> 13:59.547
Good. Though you probably
won't need them anymore

13:59.547 --> 14:01.090
once La Fiera
murders Cesar.

14:01.090 --> 14:04.093
Which she will 100% do
when she finds him.

14:04.093 --> 14:05.762
He's only got one chance,

14:05.762 --> 14:08.097
and that's to make a deal
with us ‐‐

14:08.097 --> 14:09.724
witness protection.

14:09.724 --> 14:12.435
He won't go for it.

14:12.435 --> 14:14.270
He's too proud to be seen
as a rat.

14:14.270 --> 14:16.147
Well, then it's your job
to convince him

14:16.147 --> 14:19.400
it's not snitching
when you torpedo your enemies.

14:19.400 --> 14:21.194
And it's not snitching
to stay alive long enough

14:21.194 --> 14:24.363
to be a father
to your child.

14:24.363 --> 14:25.823
Look.

14:26.908 --> 14:28.826
There's no other way out.

14:28.826 --> 14:30.453
Just have him call me.

14:30.453 --> 14:37.794
♪♪

14:37.794 --> 14:39.295
She gonna call?

14:39.295 --> 14:41.172
She'll call Cesar.
Whether or not he calls me...

14:41.172 --> 14:42.423
I don't know.
[ Bell dings ]

14:42.423 --> 14:43.633
Clerk: Hey, stop!
Hey, hey, hey!

14:43.633 --> 14:45.093
Stop! Hey!

14:45.093 --> 14:46.636
Hey, guys!
Shoplifter!

14:46.636 --> 14:47.929
Back to work.

14:47.929 --> 14:49.388
♪ Everyday, sitting around ♪

14:49.388 --> 14:51.015
♪ I watch it slowly fade ♪

14:51.015 --> 14:52.475
♪ The images found ♪

14:52.475 --> 14:55.394
♪ Closed eyes, closed eyes,
no, I ♪

14:55.394 --> 14:57.063
♪ Closed eyes,
closed eyes, no, I ♪

14:57.063 --> 14:59.524
Stop!
Nowhere to go!

14:59.524 --> 15:00.691
You alright?

15:00.691 --> 15:01.692
Yeah,
yeah, yeah.

15:01.692 --> 15:03.778
Just ‐‐ Ow!

15:03.778 --> 15:05.154
Just jammed my hand.

15:05.154 --> 15:06.489
I'll call an ambulance.

15:06.489 --> 15:08.282
No, don't bother.
It's just dislocated.

15:08.282 --> 15:09.867
Uh, it's happened before.
[ Handcuffs click ]

15:09.867 --> 15:11.994
One of the occupational hazards
of working construction.

15:11.994 --> 15:12.787
[ Joint cracks ]
Agh!

15:12.787 --> 15:13.788
Ooh.

15:13.788 --> 15:15.414
I'm good. I'm good.

15:15.414 --> 15:16.833
[ Groans ]
Ow. [ Inhales sharply ]

15:19.001 --> 15:20.378
As the driver,
it would be helpful

15:20.378 --> 15:21.587
to know
where we're going.

15:21.587 --> 15:22.839
You seem nervous.

15:22.839 --> 15:24.257
Nah, it's every girl's dream
to drive

15:24.257 --> 15:26.676
to an undisclosed location
with two armed men.

15:26.676 --> 15:30.179
Relax. We just need to pick up
the ingredients for the cook.

15:30.179 --> 15:33.141
"Pick up."
You mean steal?

15:33.141 --> 15:34.475
Just keep
driving straight.

15:34.475 --> 15:35.768
[ Door buzzer ]

15:35.768 --> 15:37.770
Del Monte: I'm just asking
for a little help, okay?

15:37.770 --> 15:39.772
It makes my job a lot harder
when the paperwork isn't right.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.482
Sgt. Grey: Nolan!

15:41.482 --> 15:44.026
You okay? So, I heard you got
injured in your foot pursuit.

15:44.026 --> 15:45.862
Oh, I just dislocated
my finger.

15:45.862 --> 15:47.196
My nondominant hand.

15:47.196 --> 15:48.990
Uh, be sore for a couple days ‐‐
I'll be good to go.

15:48.990 --> 15:51.868
That guy assaulted you?
No, I slipped
when we came ‐‐

15:51.868 --> 15:53.244
[ Cellphone rings]
Oh, excuse me for a second.

15:53.244 --> 15:54.620
Hey, Judge,
thanks for calling.

15:54.620 --> 15:56.539
Listen, don't worry.
I got your back.

15:56.539 --> 15:57.665
Thanks.
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, not you.

15:57.665 --> 15:59.167
Make sure you document
the injury.

15:59.167 --> 16:00.668
It might seem like
it's nothing now,

16:00.668 --> 16:02.253
but turn into an issue
down the road,

16:02.253 --> 16:03.171
you need
a paper trail.

16:03.171 --> 16:04.088
Yes, sir.

16:04.088 --> 16:05.464
Oh.
Um, incidentally,

16:05.464 --> 16:07.675
I spoke to Reyna ‐‐
Cesar's girlfriend.

16:07.675 --> 16:08.968
I think there's a chance
he'll reach out.

16:08.968 --> 16:11.053
The optimism of a rookie.

16:11.053 --> 16:13.806
It burns bright,
and then it's gone forever.

16:13.806 --> 16:15.808
Hey, Nolan.
Our guy just peed himself.

16:15.808 --> 16:16.934
Take care of that,
will ya?

16:18.686 --> 16:20.479
[ Laughs ]

16:22.106 --> 16:23.691
Tamara: This place
is beautiful.

16:23.691 --> 16:25.276
Silas: They really shouldn't
leave standing water like that.

16:25.276 --> 16:28.029
It attracts mosquitoes,
and mosquitoes carry disease.

16:28.029 --> 16:29.530
We'll make sure that's running
before the wedding.

16:29.530 --> 16:31.240
And hire
an exterminator.

16:31.240 --> 16:33.034
Sorry,
w‐we're closed for repairs.

16:33.034 --> 16:34.577
We saw that
on your website.

16:34.577 --> 16:36.662
Which means you have nothing
booked for Saturday.

16:36.662 --> 16:38.581
Right. Because we're closed
for repairs.

16:38.581 --> 16:40.291
A pipe burst.
There was extensive damage.

16:40.291 --> 16:42.251
We know.
We saw it on your website.

16:42.251 --> 16:44.670
So Mr. Nolan reached out
to your contractor

16:44.670 --> 16:45.880
and arranged some friends

16:45.880 --> 16:47.548
to come get this damage fixed
by Saturday.

16:47.548 --> 16:49.258
He ‐‐ He what?

16:49.258 --> 16:51.010
Mrs. Evers' son Wesley
is getting married here

16:51.010 --> 16:52.386
on Saturday.

16:52.386 --> 16:54.263
It won't be a big wedding,
'cause it's last‐minute

16:54.263 --> 16:55.556
and people won't be able
to travel.

16:55.556 --> 16:57.475
But w‐we're closed ‐‐
you can't ‐‐

16:57.475 --> 16:59.894
Oh, of course we can.
And we did.

16:59.894 --> 17:02.063
And I'm gonna expect
a discount,

17:02.063 --> 17:03.981
since you'll be able
to start holding events here

17:03.981 --> 17:05.816
weeks ahead of schedule.

17:05.816 --> 17:08.277
Now, let's you and I discuss
what you'll be able

17:08.277 --> 17:09.904
to provide
on short notice

17:09.904 --> 17:12.156
and what I'm gonna
have to bring in.

17:12.156 --> 17:15.409
Look, I don't know
what Aldo told you about me,

17:15.409 --> 17:16.911
but this isn't what I do,
okay?

17:16.911 --> 17:19.080
I ‐‐ I'm a chemist.

17:19.080 --> 17:21.082
I‐I don't know how to pull off
a ‐‐ a heist.

17:21.082 --> 17:22.583
Half‐Life: A heist?

17:22.583 --> 17:24.293
Oh, that's way fancier
than what we're gonna do.

17:24.293 --> 17:26.712
Nah, this is gonna be a lot of,
"Get on the floor!

17:26.712 --> 17:28.172
This is a robbery!

17:28.172 --> 17:30.550
Don't move,
or I'll kill you!"

17:30.550 --> 17:32.760
You're coming to make sure
we steal the right stuff.

17:32.760 --> 17:36.138
Well, look, I have a contact
who can get us what we need.

17:36.138 --> 17:37.014
It'll just take
a few days ‐‐

17:37.014 --> 17:39.058
We don't have a few days.

17:39.058 --> 17:40.851
If we don't deliver
the product we owe,

17:40.851 --> 17:42.895
things go badly
for all of us.

17:42.895 --> 17:45.481
Besides, why pay when we can
steal it for free?

17:49.443 --> 17:50.486
[ Engine revving ]

17:50.486 --> 17:52.905
[ Horn honking ]

17:52.905 --> 17:53.906
Light 'em up.

17:53.906 --> 17:55.616
[ Siren wailing ]

17:55.616 --> 18:01.706
♪♪

18:01.706 --> 18:07.878
♪♪

18:07.878 --> 18:09.130
Damn it.

18:10.214 --> 18:11.632
It's Lucy.

18:11.632 --> 18:12.883
What do we do?

18:12.883 --> 18:14.385
Treat it like
any other stop,

18:14.385 --> 18:17.513
but we do not run anyone
in that car.

18:17.513 --> 18:19.056
Dahrio:
Lean back in your seat.
[ Gun clicks ]

18:19.056 --> 18:20.474
What are you doing?

18:20.474 --> 18:22.852
You're out on bail,
Half‐Life's got a warrant,

18:22.852 --> 18:24.520
and this ride is stolen.

18:24.520 --> 18:27.523
There's no way these cops
are gonna let us go.

18:27.523 --> 18:29.525
When I pop this guy,
bail out and cap his partner.

18:29.525 --> 18:31.652
W‐Wait, wait, wait, wait.

18:31.652 --> 18:34.280
Look, before we start shooting
cops in broad daylight,

18:34.280 --> 18:36.449
can ‐‐ just let me
try something, okay?

18:36.449 --> 18:38.075
What?

18:38.075 --> 18:40.453
Flirting.

18:40.453 --> 18:42.246
I haven't gotten a ticket
since I was 16.

18:42.246 --> 18:43.289
I know
how to get out of them.

18:43.289 --> 18:45.207
Okay?
Just ‐‐ Just trust me.

18:47.835 --> 18:49.920
I'm sorry, Officer.

18:49.920 --> 18:51.547
Was I going too fast?

18:51.547 --> 18:52.715
Yes, ma'am.

18:52.715 --> 18:54.425
You almost caused
an accident.

18:54.425 --> 18:56.260
We're in a hurry.
It's my brother's birthday,

18:56.260 --> 18:58.763
and I haven't gotten
any party supplies.

19:01.265 --> 19:02.516
License and registration,
please.

19:02.516 --> 19:05.853
C'mon, you don't really
need that, do you?

19:05.853 --> 19:08.689
You should come to the party
after work.

19:08.689 --> 19:09.982
We'd have fun.

19:13.527 --> 19:15.071
[ Chuckles ]

19:15.071 --> 19:16.447
Yeah.

19:16.447 --> 19:17.865
I bet we would.

19:17.865 --> 19:24.580
♪♪

19:24.580 --> 19:26.957
Alright, I'm gonna let you go
with a warning this time.

19:26.957 --> 19:28.709
But slow down.
Okay?

19:28.709 --> 19:30.294
Yeah, I promise.

19:30.294 --> 19:31.420
Thank you so much.

19:31.420 --> 19:33.214
Yeah.

19:33.214 --> 19:34.924
Have fun at that party.

19:39.845 --> 19:42.598
[ Sighs ] See?

19:42.598 --> 19:44.517
Cops are easy ‐‐ you just got to
know how to play them.

19:48.020 --> 19:49.730
[ Engine starts ]

19:51.273 --> 19:54.235
[ Cellphone beeps,
line rings ]

19:54.235 --> 19:55.778
Harper: <i>What's up?</i>
We just pulled over Lucy

19:55.778 --> 19:58.072
<i>in a red SUV,</i>
<i>definitely stolen.</i>

19:58.072 --> 19:59.281
She was with
two serious‐looking men.

19:59.281 --> 20:00.658
Any idea where they're going?

20:00.658 --> 20:02.493
Negative. But she said
they were picking up supplies

20:02.493 --> 20:04.412
for her brother's party.

20:04.412 --> 20:06.706
Uh, Salonga has a brother ‐‐
Dahrio.

20:06.706 --> 20:09.417
Uh, she could mean
he's who's with her.

20:09.417 --> 20:11.794
And party supplies obviously
means ingredients for a cook.

20:11.794 --> 20:12.962
<i>Where are you?</i>

20:12.962 --> 20:13.879
Uh,
south of Wilshire Park.

20:16.048 --> 20:17.591
[ Computer beeps ]

20:17.591 --> 20:19.135
Alright, there are
three chemical storage

20:19.135 --> 20:21.011
supply companies
in that vicinity.

20:21.011 --> 20:22.638
Well, they're gonna rob
one of them.

20:22.638 --> 20:24.473
And we're gonna
let it happen.

20:24.473 --> 20:25.599
[ Sighs ]

20:25.599 --> 20:27.268
[ Cellphone beeps ]

20:32.481 --> 20:34.817
[ Tires squeal ]

20:40.990 --> 20:42.491
[ Brakes squeak ]

20:42.491 --> 20:45.786
[ Gearshift clicks,
engine shuts off ]

20:45.786 --> 20:47.913
Alright.
Here we go.

20:47.913 --> 20:49.123
Why do I have to go in?

20:49.123 --> 20:50.040
I can just write down
what I need.

20:50.040 --> 20:52.001
I'm a cook, not a crook.

20:52.001 --> 20:54.420
You're whatever I say
you are.

20:54.420 --> 20:57.673
Hey, if anybody gets hurt,
I am out.

20:57.673 --> 20:58.924
That's not how it works.

20:58.924 --> 21:01.594
You can't only be in the game
a little.

21:01.594 --> 21:02.887
That's how you get killed.

21:02.887 --> 21:04.638
Now come on.

21:04.638 --> 21:08.225
[ METZ's "Blind Youth
Industrial Park" plays ]

21:08.225 --> 21:09.602
[ Vehicle door closes ]

21:09.602 --> 21:16.108
♪♪

21:16.108 --> 21:17.526
Dahrio: Go, go, go, go,
go, go, go!

21:17.526 --> 21:21.280
♪♪

21:21.280 --> 21:22.740
Don't move!
[ Shotgun cocks ]

21:22.740 --> 21:24.909
Don't move!
Everyone down, right now!

21:24.909 --> 21:26.035
Right now!

21:26.035 --> 21:30.581
[ All shouting indistinctly ]

21:30.581 --> 21:33.918
♪ A new distorted lens
to look through ♪

21:33.918 --> 21:35.878
Oh, oh!
Don't. Don't!

21:35.878 --> 21:37.296
Don't do it!

21:37.296 --> 21:39.507
Unless you want
a closed‐casket funeral!

21:39.507 --> 21:41.425
Touch that gun and you're dead,
you hear me?

21:42.384 --> 21:44.094
Don't make me kill you!

21:44.094 --> 21:46.096
Come on! Down!

21:46.096 --> 21:50.392
♪ I've never seen a sight
that looked so beautiful ♪

21:50.392 --> 21:52.561
Hey, what are you doing?
Get her.

21:52.561 --> 21:54.730
[ Sobbing ]
Don't hurt me. Don't.

21:54.730 --> 21:57.525
I'm not gonna hurt you.
Just sit down right here.

21:57.525 --> 21:58.818
Sit down.

22:00.653 --> 22:02.071
Half‐Life: Hey, mama.

22:02.071 --> 22:04.114
Hey.
[ Gasping ]

22:04.114 --> 22:05.699
You're a sexy one,
aren't you?

22:05.699 --> 22:07.576
[ Crying ]

22:07.576 --> 22:08.994
Dahrio: Watch them.

22:08.994 --> 22:10.913
Anyone as much as twitches,
blow their brains out.

22:10.913 --> 22:12.748
Let's go.

22:12.748 --> 22:14.625
Nova, let's go!

22:18.212 --> 22:20.130
[ Cellphone rings ]

22:21.841 --> 22:23.884
Tell me.
Dispatch: <i>A silent alarm</i>
<i>was just triggered</i>

22:23.884 --> 22:25.344
<i>at Sutherland Chemical.</i>

22:25.344 --> 22:27.221
<i>Do you want us</i>
<i>to alert available units?</i>

22:27.221 --> 22:29.431
Yes, but advise them
to keep clear of the area

22:29.431 --> 22:30.391
until further notice.

22:30.391 --> 22:31.976
And get an airship over there

22:31.976 --> 22:34.937
so we can see where they go
when they leave.

22:34.937 --> 22:36.647
[ Cellphone beeps ]

22:36.647 --> 22:38.148
[ Sighs ]

22:38.148 --> 22:39.400
[ Truck beeping in distance ]

22:39.400 --> 22:43.070
[ Crying ]

22:43.070 --> 22:48.117
♪♪

22:48.117 --> 22:49.952
Half‐Life: I might
just take you with us.

22:49.952 --> 22:51.745
Would you like that?

22:51.745 --> 22:53.873
Cathy: [ Sobbing ]
Come on, baby.

22:53.873 --> 22:55.541
Dahrio: That's it?

22:55.541 --> 22:57.501
Lucy: Uh, yeah. And ‐‐
And then we're done.

22:57.501 --> 22:58.711
Dahrio: I'll grab one.
You get the other one.

22:58.711 --> 22:59.795
Lucy: I got a bad back.

22:59.795 --> 23:01.547
I don't care.

23:01.547 --> 23:03.966
Half‐Life: We'll see how scared
you can get.

23:03.966 --> 23:06.594
♪♪

23:06.594 --> 23:08.554
[ Grunts ]

23:08.554 --> 23:16.353
♪♪

23:16.353 --> 23:17.813
What are you doing?

23:17.813 --> 23:19.565
Roll it out here.
Uh...

23:19.565 --> 23:21.150
Yeah, you take it
the rest of the way.

23:21.150 --> 23:22.693
I'll go get Half‐Life.

23:24.236 --> 23:25.654
Hey.
We're out of here.

23:25.654 --> 23:26.864
Let's go.

23:26.864 --> 23:28.699
Oh, but we were just
getting friendly.

23:28.699 --> 23:30.284
Yeah,
let's go right now.

23:30.284 --> 23:32.077
Don't touch me.

23:32.077 --> 23:33.579
Dahrio: Hey!

23:33.579 --> 23:35.039
Let's move!

23:35.039 --> 23:36.832
♪♪

23:36.832 --> 23:38.959
See you soon.

23:38.959 --> 23:47.176
♪♪

23:47.176 --> 23:48.260
It's over.

23:48.260 --> 23:50.262
They stole the precursors
for meth.

23:50.262 --> 23:51.597
No one was hurt.

23:51.597 --> 23:52.932
From the security footage,

23:52.932 --> 23:55.434
Lucy navigated policy
and procedure perfectly.

23:56.560 --> 23:59.480
She avoided crossing the
threshold with stolen property.

23:59.480 --> 24:00.940
Where is she now?

24:00.940 --> 24:02.608
I don't know.
[ Sighs ]

24:02.608 --> 24:04.902
The airship didn't get there
in time,

24:04.902 --> 24:08.030
and Dahrio had
a switch vehicle nearby.

24:08.030 --> 24:09.949
We lost her.

24:09.949 --> 24:13.327
Nolan: Well, this is where Reyna
said Cesar is hiding out.

24:13.327 --> 24:14.828
Smitty: I don't even know
why you're still working.

24:14.828 --> 24:16.956
A busted finger gets you
a week off at least.
[ Door opens ]

24:16.956 --> 24:18.791
[ Rap music plays in building ]

24:18.791 --> 24:20.209
[ Door closes ]

24:20.209 --> 24:21.085
Cesar.

24:22.670 --> 24:24.630
Don't run.

24:24.630 --> 24:26.215
Reyna told us
where to find you.

24:26.215 --> 24:27.675
She shouldn't have
done that.

24:27.675 --> 24:28.968
I'm not making a deal.

24:28.968 --> 24:32.554
♪♪

24:32.554 --> 24:33.722
Sniper!

24:33.722 --> 24:34.640
[ Gunshot ]

24:34.640 --> 24:44.441
♪♪

24:44.441 --> 24:46.068
[ Walkie talkie blips ]

24:46.068 --> 24:47.528
7‐Adam‐15, shots fired.

24:47.528 --> 24:49.113
Shooter is on the roof
of a building

24:49.113 --> 24:51.949
one block west
of 9731 Hickory.

24:51.949 --> 24:52.866
[ Sirens wailing ]

24:52.866 --> 24:54.576
He's on the run.

24:54.576 --> 24:58.706
Requesting backup and R. A. unit
for a gunshot victim ‐‐

24:58.706 --> 24:59.289
Not conscious.
Not breathing.

25:04.795 --> 25:05.838
You two alright?

25:05.838 --> 25:08.215
22 years on the job
without incident.

25:08.215 --> 25:10.551
One shift
with the unlucky charm ‐‐

25:10.551 --> 25:12.011
a freaking sniper.

25:13.762 --> 25:16.306
I need a moment.

25:16.306 --> 25:17.641
Did you manage to track
the shooter?

25:17.641 --> 25:19.435
No. He even took
his shell casing.

25:19.435 --> 25:21.145
But it's gotta be
La Fiera's doing.

25:21.145 --> 25:23.105
And now that she's gotten
her revenge,

25:23.105 --> 25:24.481
I'll bet she'll head home
to Guatemala,

25:24.481 --> 25:26.817
lay low in friendly territory
until the dust settles.

25:26.817 --> 25:28.318
She was tracing
Reyna's calls.

25:28.318 --> 25:29.528
Most likely.

25:29.528 --> 25:30.988
And I led her
straight to him.

25:30.988 --> 25:32.031
Don't do that to yourself.

25:32.031 --> 25:33.365
You were trying to do
the right thing.

25:33.365 --> 25:34.241
It's not your fault.

25:34.241 --> 25:36.201
I'm ‐‐
[ Cellphone rings ]

25:36.201 --> 25:37.703
I'm sorry,
will you excuse me?

25:37.703 --> 25:39.288
I have an ADA problem.

25:41.498 --> 25:42.791
Okay,
we should have stopped it.

25:42.791 --> 25:43.959
It was my call.

25:43.959 --> 25:45.711
And Lucy handled herself
like a pro.

25:45.711 --> 25:47.296
She was hot‐walking
those guys around

25:47.296 --> 25:48.922
like she had been doing it
for years.

25:48.922 --> 25:51.258
She is clear that
if she is in over her head,

25:51.258 --> 25:52.551
she can pull herself out.

25:52.551 --> 25:53.969
She won't,
and you know it.

25:53.969 --> 25:55.345
There's no quit in Chen.

25:55.345 --> 25:56.889
Look, she's due for a check‐in
at midnight.

25:56.889 --> 25:58.474
I will take
her temperature then.

25:58.474 --> 26:00.100
If I feel like
she is in too deep,

26:00.100 --> 26:01.727
then we can go get her.

26:01.727 --> 26:02.811
Call me right after.

26:02.811 --> 26:04.104
Alright.

26:04.104 --> 26:05.314
Now I gotta go
to my second job ‐‐

26:05.314 --> 26:07.524
planning Lopez's
emergency wedding.

26:07.524 --> 26:09.568
Jackson: Uh, plates and flatware
are under "food," right?

26:09.568 --> 26:11.528
Yes. Even though we don't eat
the plates,

26:11.528 --> 26:12.780
they still fall under
the food category.

26:12.780 --> 26:13.906
Copy that.

26:13.906 --> 26:15.866
Great.
So, that leaves...

26:15.866 --> 26:17.451
Flowers, music,
an officiant,

26:17.451 --> 26:19.161
the cake,
and the marriage license.

26:19.161 --> 26:21.163
Nope. Picked up the license
during lunch.

26:21.163 --> 26:22.331
And I got the music.

26:22.331 --> 26:24.041
My performing arts teacher
is a cellist.

26:24.041 --> 26:26.001
I told her to learn
the "Wedding March"
and some Cardi B.

26:26.001 --> 26:27.920
Who?
Uh, never mind.

26:27.920 --> 26:29.004
She's ‐‐ She's joking.

26:29.004 --> 26:31.590
I ‐‐ I feel bad.

26:31.590 --> 26:33.383
W‐Why?

26:33.383 --> 26:35.260
Well, this is
for something special.

26:35.260 --> 26:36.178
Tamara and I are doing it
for money.

26:36.178 --> 26:37.304
It doesn't feel right.

26:37.304 --> 26:38.931
Oh, nonsense.

26:38.931 --> 26:40.557
You two are providing
a service.

26:40.557 --> 26:42.893
It has value,
and you should get paid for it.

26:42.893 --> 26:44.853
It doesn't make your help
any less special.

26:44.853 --> 26:46.688
Or appreciated.
Okay?

26:46.688 --> 26:48.107
Okay.

26:48.107 --> 26:49.817
Seriously,
who is Cardi B?

26:49.817 --> 26:51.026
Let me show you a video.

26:51.026 --> 26:52.569
Unh‐unh. No.

26:52.569 --> 26:53.487
Nolan:
Ah, Mr. Del Monte.

26:53.487 --> 26:54.488
Uh, y‐you have a second?

26:54.488 --> 26:55.614
Ah, Nolan.
Uh, not really.

26:55.614 --> 26:56.740
Actually, I'm kind of late
for dinner.

26:56.740 --> 26:58.450
You charged my shoplifter
with felony assault.

26:58.450 --> 26:59.910
Why?

26:59.910 --> 27:01.787
[ Sighs ]
Look at your hand.

27:01.787 --> 27:03.038
I slipped and fell.

27:03.038 --> 27:05.290
While in pursuit
of the suspect.

27:05.290 --> 27:06.750
Wouldn't have happened if
he hadn't committed the crime.

27:06.750 --> 27:08.335
He committed
a misdemeanor.

27:08.335 --> 27:10.587
We can't up‐charge him to
a felony because I was clumsy.

27:10.587 --> 27:12.422
No, relax.
It's not gonna go to trial.

27:12.422 --> 27:13.715
This guy's
gonna plead out.

27:13.715 --> 27:16.260
I'll knock it down
to, like, reckless endangerment.

27:16.260 --> 27:18.345
He'll get a couple years'
probation, tops. It's fine.

27:18.345 --> 27:20.222
And a felony on his record,
which will affect

27:20.222 --> 27:21.807
every aspect of his life
from here on out.

27:21.807 --> 27:23.141
How can that be justice?

27:23.141 --> 27:24.726
Okay, look, I know
you're still new to all this,

27:24.726 --> 27:27.104
but that's exactly what it is ‐‐
it's justice.

27:27.104 --> 27:28.397
And actually,
last time I checked,

27:28.397 --> 27:30.232
I had a pretty
sterling reputation

27:30.232 --> 27:31.525
with your police union,
so...

27:31.525 --> 27:34.111
It's still wrong,
and you know it.

27:34.111 --> 27:36.572
How about this ‐‐

27:36.572 --> 27:38.657
I won't tell you
how to arrest them,

27:38.657 --> 27:41.285
and you don't tell me
how to charge them.

27:41.285 --> 27:42.494
Good talk.

27:42.494 --> 27:45.622
[ Car alarm chirps ]

27:45.622 --> 27:47.499
[ Car door opens ]

27:47.499 --> 27:49.167
[ Door opens ]

27:49.167 --> 27:50.252
Nolan: You made it!
Come in!

27:50.252 --> 27:52.963
Thank you, again.
I washed it.

27:52.963 --> 27:54.131
Oh, you didn't have
to do that.

27:54.131 --> 27:55.966
Oh, good,
'cause I didn't.

27:55.966 --> 27:57.593
Seconds ago,
on your doorstep,

27:57.593 --> 27:59.219
I realized a better person
would've washed it,

27:59.219 --> 28:01.263
so I said I did, but...

28:01.263 --> 28:03.015
now I'm caught
in a tangle of lies.

28:03.015 --> 28:03.807
[ Laughs ]

28:03.807 --> 28:06.101
Bailey, this is Fiona.

28:06.101 --> 28:07.394
Hello.

28:07.394 --> 28:09.646
Hi. I‐I didn't realize
it was a party.

28:09.646 --> 28:11.106
A party?
Nolan: No. Uh, sorry.

28:11.106 --> 28:13.358
I w‐would've
called you, um,

28:13.358 --> 28:15.903
but I don't know your last name
and I didn't have your number.

28:15.903 --> 28:18.614
Uh, Fiona Ryan is my ethics
and law professor.

28:18.614 --> 28:20.824
She's helping me
with an emergency work issue.

28:20.824 --> 28:21.909
But you're welcome
to stay.

28:21.909 --> 28:23.535
I‐I want you to stay.

28:23.535 --> 28:24.494
Will there still be food?

28:24.494 --> 28:25.704
Yes.
Then I'll stay.

28:25.704 --> 28:26.955
Excellent choice.

28:28.790 --> 28:30.500
So, what's the issue?

28:30.500 --> 28:32.878
John just became aware
of the systemic problem

28:32.878 --> 28:35.088
of overcharging
in the justice system.

28:35.088 --> 28:37.841
Okay, when you say it like that,
you make me sound naive.

28:37.841 --> 28:39.217
I had a wobbler today.

28:39.217 --> 28:40.594
It's a crime
that could be charged

28:40.594 --> 28:42.679
either as a misdemeanor
or a felony.

28:42.679 --> 28:44.848
Yes, and the ADA went ahead
and charged it as a felony

28:44.848 --> 28:46.308
even though
it was not one.

28:46.308 --> 28:49.561
Things are so much more simple
in the UCMJ.

28:49.561 --> 28:51.647
Uniform Code
of Military Justice.

28:51.647 --> 28:53.565
I thought
you were a firefighter.

28:53.565 --> 28:56.610
I am. I'm also a reserve
in the Army National Guard.

28:56.610 --> 28:58.570
And a capoeira instructor,

28:58.570 --> 29:00.238
in case you ever want to
learn dance fighting.

29:00.238 --> 29:02.616
Ooh,
I love dance fighting.

29:02.616 --> 29:04.826
Oh, it's the most
excellent workout.

29:04.826 --> 29:07.329
I do it every Thursday night
after I volunteer at the ACLU.

29:07.329 --> 29:08.497
Okay,
between the two of you,

29:08.497 --> 29:10.374
I'm officially starting
to feel like a slacker.

29:10.374 --> 29:12.042
[ Laughs ] Good.

29:12.042 --> 29:13.877
So, why can't you just go
to this D. A. guy

29:13.877 --> 29:15.420
and ask him
not to charge a felony?

29:15.420 --> 29:16.797
Well, cops don't decide
on the charges.

29:16.797 --> 29:18.131
The D. A.'s office
does that.

29:18.131 --> 29:20.926
Oh, do not leave out
the department's complicity

29:20.926 --> 29:22.844
in this problem, John.

29:22.844 --> 29:25.222
Police officers are ordered
to write up

29:25.222 --> 29:27.224
almost all wobblers
as felonies.

29:27.224 --> 29:29.434
Mm.
Not ordered.
Strongly encouraged.

29:29.434 --> 29:31.436
[ Scoffs ]
And where we don't,

29:31.436 --> 29:34.773
the D. A. almost always upcharges
to the felony anyway.

29:34.773 --> 29:36.233
So, what are you gonna do?

29:36.233 --> 29:38.443
And don't let the fact
that this decision will tell me

29:38.443 --> 29:40.112
everything I need to know
about you as a person

29:40.112 --> 29:41.571
sway your choice.

29:41.571 --> 29:44.491
[ Laughs ]
Oh, I like her.

29:44.491 --> 29:46.952
I like you.
Mm‐hmm.

29:46.952 --> 29:47.703
Harper: Lucy missed
her check‐in.

29:47.703 --> 29:49.079
She's cooking.

29:49.079 --> 29:50.205
You don't know that
for sure.

29:50.205 --> 29:51.415
She's either cooking
or she's dead.

29:51.415 --> 29:52.457
She's not dead.

29:52.457 --> 29:53.959
Then she's making product.

29:53.959 --> 29:56.086
From the chemicals she stole,
we know it's meth.

29:56.086 --> 29:59.006
Alright, that takes
four to eight hours.

29:59.006 --> 30:01.008
Look, you and I both know
it's against the law

30:01.008 --> 30:03.802
for her to allow product
she cooked to hit the streets.

30:03.802 --> 30:06.805
If we don't find her, she's
gonna stop it by herself...

30:06.805 --> 30:08.223
or die trying.

30:09.641 --> 30:11.643
[ Sighs ]

30:11.643 --> 30:12.894
Are you done?

30:12.894 --> 30:14.271
No.
I'm just getting started.

30:14.271 --> 30:15.522
It's gonna take me
all night.

30:15.522 --> 30:17.899
Why? You've been at it
for three hours already.

30:17.899 --> 30:19.693
I want it finished
and out the door by sunrise.

30:19.693 --> 30:21.486
Yeah, and I want a mansion
and a yacht,

30:21.486 --> 30:22.904
but I'm dealing
with chemicals that explode

30:22.904 --> 30:25.198
if you look at them funny,
so I'll take the time I need.

30:27.034 --> 30:29.745
It's out by sunrise,

30:29.745 --> 30:30.746
or it's over.

30:37.502 --> 30:44.634
♪♪

30:44.634 --> 30:51.308
♪♪

30:54.269 --> 31:01.735
♪♪

31:01.735 --> 31:08.784
♪♪

31:08.784 --> 31:16.083
♪♪

31:16.083 --> 31:17.542
Where's the rest of it?

31:17.542 --> 31:19.377
The lab you built me
was undersized,

31:19.377 --> 31:21.171
so I only had enough time
to make one batch.

31:21.171 --> 31:23.340
Why the hell
are you telling me that now?

31:23.340 --> 31:25.717
'Cause I wasn't in the mood
to have this conversation.

31:25.717 --> 31:27.761
[ Grunts ]

31:27.761 --> 31:29.513
I'm done
with your attitude.

31:29.513 --> 31:32.140
I can find another cook.

31:32.140 --> 31:34.392
Wait, wait.
Look, I'm sorry.

31:34.392 --> 31:36.770
It's ‐‐
It's been a long night.

31:36.770 --> 31:38.814
But I can make some more.

31:38.814 --> 31:40.565
And it'll be quicker this time.
I promise.

31:40.565 --> 31:41.942
Do it.

31:41.942 --> 31:44.111
But I'm not waiting.

31:44.111 --> 31:46.404
Half‐Life will stay
while you cook.

31:46.404 --> 31:48.865
I gotta get this
out on the street.

31:48.865 --> 31:50.450
It should all
go out together.

31:50.450 --> 31:53.620
♪♪

31:53.620 --> 31:54.746
Why?

31:54.746 --> 31:55.747
[ Gunfire ]

31:55.747 --> 31:57.624
[ Indistinct shouting ]

32:03.088 --> 32:04.297
[ Man screams ]

32:04.297 --> 32:06.216
[ Gunfire ]

32:06.216 --> 32:15.308
♪♪

32:15.308 --> 32:16.852
Aah!

32:16.852 --> 32:19.062
♪♪

32:19.062 --> 32:20.355
[ Cellphone dialing, rings ]

32:20.355 --> 32:22.065
Hey. It's me.

32:22.065 --> 32:24.234
La Fiera's here.
Mission Road ‐‐ hurry.

32:27.696 --> 32:28.822
Okay, I‐I give up,
I give up!

32:28.822 --> 32:31.992
<i>iNo más! iNo más!</i>

32:31.992 --> 32:33.702
It's okay. It's okay.
Amiga.

32:33.702 --> 32:35.120
Amiga!

32:35.120 --> 32:36.413
Sandra: Amiga, huh?

32:36.413 --> 32:38.665
Who says I need
a friend?

32:38.665 --> 32:39.875
Everybody needs a friend.

32:39.875 --> 32:42.252
Especially one
with certain skills.

32:42.252 --> 32:43.545
You want to come work
for me?

32:43.545 --> 32:45.422
It's clearly
my best option.

32:45.422 --> 32:47.132
I haven't said
it was an option yet.

32:48.758 --> 32:50.177
Dahrio: [ Groans ]

32:50.177 --> 32:52.387
I hear you're running
Aldo's operation.

32:52.387 --> 32:53.680
You owe product
to the Madrigal family,

32:53.680 --> 32:55.223
which means
you owe it to me now.

32:55.223 --> 32:57.726
Sure. No problem.

32:57.726 --> 32:59.811
I can give you half
right now.

32:59.811 --> 33:01.605
It's already in the truck.

33:01.605 --> 33:03.565
And she can make the rest.

33:03.565 --> 33:07.152
She can?

33:07.152 --> 33:08.570
Then what do I need you for?

33:08.570 --> 33:09.988
Wait.

33:09.988 --> 33:15.702
♪♪

33:15.702 --> 33:17.787
You can make the rest,
right?

33:17.787 --> 33:19.456
Yes, ma'am.
There's enough chemicals here.

33:19.456 --> 33:21.291
I just...

33:21.291 --> 33:23.126
I need my hands free.

33:25.545 --> 33:26.588
[ Blade clicks ]

33:30.050 --> 33:33.261
You look familiar to me.

33:33.261 --> 33:34.721
I can't imagine why.

33:34.721 --> 33:37.390
We've never met.

33:37.390 --> 33:39.768
I'm not so sure.

33:39.768 --> 33:41.186
[ Gun cocks ]

33:41.186 --> 33:43.271
I have a very good memory
for faces.

33:43.271 --> 33:44.981
I ‐‐

33:44.981 --> 33:46.608
I swear,
I'd remember you.

33:46.608 --> 33:47.901
You're unforgettable.

33:47.901 --> 33:48.860
I'm just a nobody.

33:48.860 --> 33:51.446
[ Banging ]

33:51.446 --> 33:53.615
[ Groans ]

33:53.615 --> 33:54.658
You're not a nobody,
are you?

33:54.658 --> 33:55.909
No, I'm a cop.

33:55.909 --> 33:57.577
And you're under arrest.

33:57.577 --> 34:00.247
You stole my line.

34:00.247 --> 34:01.706
I thought you said
she needed rescuing.

34:04.459 --> 34:06.670
Turn around, <i>Hermana.</i>
Hands behind your back.

34:07.796 --> 34:09.589
I told you it was gonna end
this way.

34:09.589 --> 34:11.549
[ Police radio chatter ]

34:11.549 --> 34:13.426
You okay?

34:13.426 --> 34:16.263
Let's just go with yes.

34:16.263 --> 34:17.806
How'd you guys get here
so fast?

34:17.806 --> 34:19.391
Not that I'm complaining.

34:19.391 --> 34:20.725
When you didn't report in
last night,

34:20.725 --> 34:22.060
Sergeant Grey
called the chief,

34:22.060 --> 34:23.645
who called
every law enforcement agency

34:23.645 --> 34:24.896
in Southern California.

34:24.896 --> 34:28.024
400 cops just spent
the night looking for you.

34:28.024 --> 34:30.527
[ Exhales sharply ] Wow.

34:32.529 --> 34:33.947
I told you
to leave it alone.

34:33.947 --> 34:36.032
You did.
And I didn't.

34:36.032 --> 34:37.450
And now he's got me
on his side.

34:39.953 --> 34:41.538
Okay, fine.

34:41.538 --> 34:43.290
I'll ‐‐ I'll knock down

34:43.290 --> 34:45.583
the assault charge
on his shoplifter.

34:45.583 --> 34:46.960
Not good enough.

34:46.960 --> 34:48.003
I just got off the phone
with three other

34:48.003 --> 34:49.796
division watch commanders.

34:49.796 --> 34:52.215
As of tomorrow,
we're instructing
all our officers

34:52.215 --> 34:54.759
to treat wobblers
as a misdemeanor,

34:54.759 --> 34:56.553
never a felony,

34:56.553 --> 34:58.680
unless there's
damn good reason to.

34:58.680 --> 35:00.265
Nolan: And if you keep
overcharging,

35:00.265 --> 35:01.474
you're gonna lose
the cooperation

35:01.474 --> 35:03.435
of the arresting officers.

35:03.435 --> 35:06.479
Good luck making a plea deal
after that.

35:06.479 --> 35:08.231
[ Chuckles ]

35:08.231 --> 35:10.025
Expect a call
from the D. A.

35:10.025 --> 35:11.109
Maybe even the mayor.

35:11.109 --> 35:12.736
They have the number.

35:12.736 --> 35:15.655
And you ‐‐ don't ever come
calling for a favor.

35:18.617 --> 35:21.620
You just made an enemy
at the D. A.'s office.

35:21.620 --> 35:22.662
Was it worth it?

35:22.662 --> 35:23.747
Absolutely, sir.

35:23.747 --> 35:24.873
[ Chuckles ] Good.

35:24.873 --> 35:25.874
Get back to work.

35:25.874 --> 35:27.292
[ Buzzer ]

35:27.292 --> 35:28.752
I'll be out of here
before you know it.

35:28.752 --> 35:30.253
No, you won't.

35:30.253 --> 35:32.464
You can lie to yourself about it
if you want,

35:32.464 --> 35:34.215
just like you lied to yourself
about Diego.

35:34.215 --> 35:37.344
What the hell
are you talking about?

35:37.344 --> 35:39.721
Cesar might have sent
the shooter who killed him,

35:39.721 --> 35:41.514
but you loaded the gun.

35:41.514 --> 35:43.808
You crossed a line with Diego
you said you never would.

35:43.808 --> 35:47.437
You used him as a cover to talk
to Cesar's father.

35:47.437 --> 35:49.898
You hung the target
around your son's neck.

35:49.898 --> 35:52.525
He's dead because of you,
<i>Hermana.</i>

35:52.525 --> 35:55.236
And deep down,
you know it.

35:57.030 --> 35:58.740
[ Door slams ]

35:58.740 --> 36:03.536
♪♪

36:08.833 --> 36:10.543
Lopez: This is amazing.

36:10.543 --> 36:12.170
I can't believe you pulled it
together in two days.

36:12.170 --> 36:14.130
No,
it was a team effort.

36:14.130 --> 36:16.883
Quarterbacked
by Patrice.

36:16.883 --> 36:19.177
Thank you for being there for me
during the craziness.

36:19.177 --> 36:20.720
I know
it hasn't been easy.

36:20.720 --> 36:22.472
Oh,
you owe me forever.

36:22.472 --> 36:24.182
I mean, you could save my life
like three times

36:24.182 --> 36:25.266
and we still
wouldn't be even.

36:25.266 --> 36:26.518
I know.

36:26.518 --> 36:27.769
Is there anything
I can do?

36:27.769 --> 36:29.354
Set up chairs?
Arrange flowers?

36:29.354 --> 36:30.939
No.
You're the bride.

36:30.939 --> 36:33.483
Just relax, enjoy.

36:33.483 --> 36:35.610
I need superglue,
hair pins, and your badge.

36:35.610 --> 36:36.528
Why my badge?

36:38.530 --> 36:39.322
I'll handle this.

36:39.322 --> 36:40.990
You should go get ready.

36:40.990 --> 36:42.242
This wedding
is starting on time.

36:42.242 --> 36:44.160
Yes, sir.

36:44.160 --> 36:46.079
[ Indistinct conversation ]

36:46.079 --> 36:47.706
[ Chuckles ]

36:47.706 --> 36:50.875
♪♪

36:50.875 --> 36:52.752
Mom, this is perfect.

36:52.752 --> 36:53.670
You finally used your powers
for good.

36:53.670 --> 36:55.296
[ Both laugh ]

36:55.296 --> 36:57.632
Well, it was nice having a
practice run for the real thing.

36:57.632 --> 36:59.801
I'm thinking next June
in Tuscany.

36:59.801 --> 37:02.220
No, Mom,
this is our wedding.

37:02.220 --> 37:04.597
The only wedding.
We'll see.

37:04.597 --> 37:06.766
So, we just realized
that Lopez doesn't have

37:06.766 --> 37:08.268
her something old,
something new,

37:08.268 --> 37:09.894
something borrowed,
something blue.

37:09.894 --> 37:12.480
Oh. Uh, let's see.

37:12.480 --> 37:13.565
Hmm.

37:13.565 --> 37:17.235
My grandmother wore this
at her wedding.

37:17.235 --> 37:18.570
Should be old enough,
I think.

37:18.570 --> 37:19.446
Yes. Thank you.

37:19.446 --> 37:21.072
Yeah.

37:21.072 --> 37:23.491
Oh, great, she'll be wearing
my brooch.

37:23.491 --> 37:25.702
Welcome.
Please sit wherever you like.

37:25.702 --> 37:27.203
And the bar is open.

37:27.203 --> 37:29.164
Thank you.
Thank you very much, my friend.

37:29.164 --> 37:30.373
Alright.

37:30.373 --> 37:32.500
And thank you, by the way,
for being my plus‐one.

37:32.500 --> 37:35.128
I hope it's not too weird that
our first date is a wedding.

37:35.128 --> 37:36.880
Well, technically,
our first date was a TED Talk

37:36.880 --> 37:38.506
on prosecutorial abuse.

37:38.506 --> 37:40.967
Ah. To be fair, you came
into my life wearing a towel.

37:40.967 --> 37:42.385
I felt compelled
to be unexpected.

37:42.385 --> 37:44.220
Puts a lot of pressure
on our first kiss.

37:44.220 --> 37:45.638
Good.
I like a challenge.

37:45.638 --> 37:47.724
I need
to borrow something.

37:47.724 --> 37:49.476
Oh, hi. Jackson.
Good to meet you.

37:49.476 --> 37:51.102
Bailey.
And you too.

37:51.102 --> 37:52.395
What do you need?
Doesn't matter.

37:52.395 --> 37:55.148
Ah, something borrowed.
Okay.

37:55.148 --> 37:57.776
Perfect. Henry made me this
when he was in third grade.

37:57.776 --> 37:58.902
It's my good luck charm.

37:58.902 --> 38:00.111
I'm gonna want that back.

38:00.111 --> 38:01.613
Of course. Thank you.

38:01.613 --> 38:03.573
Bye.

38:03.573 --> 38:04.949
Shall we?
Yes.

38:04.949 --> 38:06.034
[ Indistinct conversation ]

38:06.034 --> 38:09.370
Ooh!
Uh, nice pocket square, sir.

38:09.370 --> 38:12.707
Could I, um, maybe borrow it
for a few hours?

38:12.707 --> 38:14.667
What? No.

38:14.667 --> 38:16.377
It pulls together
the whole outfit.

38:16.377 --> 38:18.421
It's for Lopez, sir.

38:18.421 --> 38:21.674
♪♪

38:21.674 --> 38:24.052
[ Sighs ]

38:24.052 --> 38:26.054
It better
come back spotless.

38:26.054 --> 38:27.388
Thank you.

38:27.388 --> 38:30.517
As I was saying ‐‐
first Nolan, now Chen.

38:30.517 --> 38:33.144
Turned out to be
a pretty good teacher.

38:33.144 --> 38:35.313
Forget undercover work ‐‐ you
might have found your calling.

38:35.313 --> 38:38.733
Here's the thing, sir ‐‐
it's all my calling.

38:38.733 --> 38:41.027
If I were to go into politics
this afternoon,

38:41.027 --> 38:43.029
I would be president
in four years.

38:43.029 --> 38:45.740
I believe it.
[ Chuckles ]

38:45.740 --> 38:46.783
Officer Chen.

38:46.783 --> 38:48.326
Look at you!

38:48.326 --> 38:50.078
Triumph suits you.

38:50.078 --> 38:51.371
Thank you, sir.

38:51.371 --> 38:53.998
Thank you both
for believing in me.

38:53.998 --> 38:56.626
Well, the hardest part
is still ahead ‐‐

38:56.626 --> 38:58.253
adrenaline crash.

38:58.253 --> 38:59.754
[ Chuckles ]
Monday morning,

38:59.754 --> 39:02.549
it is back to transients
and noise complaints.
Yeah.

39:02.549 --> 39:04.634
To tell the truth,
I kind of missed it.

39:06.845 --> 39:08.555
Um, will you excuse me?

39:08.555 --> 39:11.349
Yeah.

39:11.349 --> 39:14.602
♪ Mary, she's not weeping
no more, no ♪

39:14.602 --> 39:17.021
Hey.

39:17.021 --> 39:18.439
Nice suit.

39:18.439 --> 39:20.358
Nova would be impressed.

39:20.358 --> 39:21.943
Nova was
a little thirsty.

39:21.943 --> 39:23.653
I like to think of her
as assertive.

39:23.653 --> 39:25.864
Mm.
[ Chuckles ]

39:25.864 --> 39:29.826
First solo op, and you take down
two major drug traffickers.

39:29.826 --> 39:32.495
Not bad.

39:32.495 --> 39:34.038
Thank you.

39:37.083 --> 39:38.209
Hey, Chen.

39:38.209 --> 39:39.711
Yeah?

39:39.711 --> 39:41.087
Save me a dance.

39:41.087 --> 39:44.340
♪♪

39:44.340 --> 39:45.717
[ Knock on door ]

39:45.717 --> 39:46.801
♪ I'm the sick light
of a hurricane's eye ♪

39:46.801 --> 39:48.428
Come in.

39:48.428 --> 39:51.514
♪ I'm a violent lullaby ♪

39:51.514 --> 39:53.725
Wow.

39:53.725 --> 39:56.227
Stop.
I feel enormous.

39:56.227 --> 39:58.855
No, you look amazing.

40:01.107 --> 40:02.317
What have you got
for me?

40:02.317 --> 40:03.610
Oh! Yes.

40:03.610 --> 40:05.570
Uh, something old ‐‐

40:05.570 --> 40:08.072
Patrice's grandmother wore this
on her wedding day.

40:08.072 --> 40:09.908
Old?
That thing looks haunted.

40:09.908 --> 40:12.118
Uh, something borrowed ‐‐

40:12.118 --> 40:13.244
Nolan says this is lucky,

40:13.244 --> 40:15.079
so that should cancel out
the brooch.

40:15.079 --> 40:17.707
And something blue ‐‐

40:17.707 --> 40:19.918
from the Sarge.

40:19.918 --> 40:21.961
How am I supposed to
wear all this?

40:21.961 --> 40:23.463
Right.
[ Sighs ]

40:23.463 --> 40:25.340
♪ His soul is trapped... ♪

40:25.340 --> 40:27.342
Jackson: Alright.

40:27.342 --> 40:29.886
♪ I crawled back
in my mother's womb ♪

40:29.886 --> 40:30.845
How's that?

40:30.845 --> 40:32.805
Ridiculous.

40:32.805 --> 40:33.890
Thank you.

40:33.890 --> 40:35.016
You're welcome.

40:35.016 --> 40:36.851
You're so welcome.

40:36.851 --> 40:38.311
[ Voice breaking ] Now get out
of here before I start crying

40:38.311 --> 40:39.604
and ruin my makeup.

40:39.604 --> 40:41.981
Yes, ma'am.
Um, did you need anything else?

40:41.981 --> 40:43.316
Oh, uh, a breath mint?

40:43.316 --> 40:44.943
[ Chuckles ]

40:44.943 --> 40:46.361
Fresh pack ‐‐

40:46.361 --> 40:47.737
something new.

40:47.737 --> 40:49.238
It's like "Mary Poppins"
in there.

40:49.238 --> 40:52.825
[ Laughs ]
Oh, wedding's in 10.

40:52.825 --> 40:54.369
[ Exhales sharply ]

40:54.369 --> 40:57.330
[ "Cello Suite No. 1 in G Major"
plays ]

40:57.330 --> 41:05.463
♪♪

41:05.463 --> 41:13.846
♪♪

41:13.846 --> 41:22.271
♪♪

41:22.271 --> 41:23.356
[ Indistinct conversation ]

41:23.356 --> 41:24.857
[ Both laugh ]

41:24.857 --> 41:26.067
Have you seen Jackson?

41:26.067 --> 41:27.902
Not recently.
Is that the wedding bouquet?

41:27.902 --> 41:30.029
Yeah. I was supposed to give it
to him to take to Mrs. Lopez.

41:30.029 --> 41:31.906
Well, I can do that.

41:31.906 --> 41:33.366
There you go.
I'll be right back.

41:33.366 --> 41:34.534
Okay.
Thanks.

41:34.534 --> 41:36.035
[ Chuckles ]

41:37.203 --> 41:38.746
[ Door opens ]

41:38.746 --> 41:39.998
I'm coming!

41:39.998 --> 41:47.463
♪♪

41:47.463 --> 41:48.589
[ Knock on door ]

41:48.589 --> 41:52.093
Angela? It's John.
I got your bouquet.

41:52.093 --> 41:53.469
[ Knock on door ]

41:53.469 --> 41:55.471
Angela?

41:55.471 --> 41:57.640
♪♪

41:57.640 --> 41:59.308
Lopez?

41:59.308 --> 42:06.190
♪♪

